message: Focus on two main strategies: 1) Use 'scissors' on 'artificial, soft' ingredients (like cardboard, paper, yarn, sponge) to get a +25 item, then use 'frame' on that 'cut' item to reach +45. This is the most reliable high-value path. 2) Use 'frame' directly on 'natural, soft' ingredients (like sunflower, flower, mushroom, leaf) for a +20 item. message: Cutting 'soft' items (both natural and artificial) is a reliable way to get 25 points. Combining two 'cut' items that share many features (e.g., 'artificial, soft, cut' with another 'artificial, soft, cut') can increase value significantly (up to 50). Avoid combining 'framed' items with each other or with 'cut' items, as this often results in ruined frames and negative or very low values. Also, avoid using 'scissors' on 'natural, hard' items, as this typically creates negative value items. If you reach a 50-value item, it's generally safe to submit.

message: Focus on using 'scissors' with artificial, soft items, especially if they are already combined (e.g., yarn + ribbon then scissors for 50 value). message: The 'frame' tool works well on 'natural' ingredients (+20). The 'scissors' tool works well on 'artificial' and 'soft' ingredients (+25), but avoid using it on 'hard' artificial items.
